<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="47.[242,1399,495,1044]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Stein D. L." pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="1 - 25" refId="ref44246" refString="Stein D. L. 2005. Descriptions of four new species, redescription of Paraliparis membranaceus, and additional data on species of the fish family Liparidae (Pisces, Scorpaeniformes) from the west coast of South America and the Indian Ocean. Zootaxa 1019: 1 - 25." type="journal article" year="2005">Stein (2005)</bibRefCitation>
, information on the collection area was obscure but unequivocal (
<bibRefCitation author="Murray J." box="[1011,1156,631,656]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="797 - 1608" refId="ref42173" refString="Murray J. 1895. Report on the Scientific Results of the Voyage of HMS &quot; Challenger &quot;. A Summary of the Scientific Results, Part. 2. Her Majesty's Stationery Office, London, 797 - 1608." type="book chapter" year="1895">Murray 1895</bibRefCitation>
). Over time, erroneous reports of the occurrence of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gunther" authorityYear="1887" box="[540,727,664,688]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Liparidae" genus="Paraliparis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="membranaceus">
<emphasis box="[540,727,664,688]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">P. membranaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
accumulated in literature. In fact, Günther’s (1887) description omitted mentioning that it was from 
<collectingCountry box="[645,703,696,720]" name="Chile" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Chile</collectingCountry>
(“... off Cape 
<collectingCountry box="[864,987,696,720]" name="Saint Vincent and the Grenadines" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">St. Vincent</collectingCountry>
, Station 310 ...”). Subsequent authors did not verify the actual collection data, and even the Natural History Museum online catalogue included incorrect collection data that have subsequently been corrected (
<bibRefCitation author="Stein D. L." box="[934,1056,759,784]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="1 - 25" refId="ref44246" refString="Stein D. L. 2005. Descriptions of four new species, redescription of Paraliparis membranaceus, and additional data on species of the fish family Liparidae (Pisces, Scorpaeniformes) from the west coast of South America and the Indian Ocean. Zootaxa 1019: 1 - 25." type="journal article" year="2005">Stein 2005</bibRefCitation>
). Burke (1930) also omitted the information that the specimen was from the fjord waters of southern 
<collectingCountry box="[957,1017,792,816]" name="Chile" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Chile</collectingCountry>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Nobre A." box="[1070,1212,791,816]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" refId="ref42440" refString="Nobre A. 1935. Fauna Marinha de Portugal. I. Vertebrados (Mamiferos, Repteis e Peixes). Companhia Editora do Minho, Barcelos." type="book" year="1935">Nobre (1935)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Albuquerque R. M." pageId="47" pageNumber="48" refId="ref38043" refString="Albuquerque R. M. 1954 - 1956. Peixes de Portugal e Ilhas Adjacentes (Chaves para a sua determinacao). Portugaliae Acta Biologica, Lisboa." type="book" year="1954">
Albuquerque (
<date box="[249,303,823,847]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="1954" valueMax="1956">1954</date>
</bibRefCitation>
–1956) referred to Günther and Burke. Still later, Lindberg (1973) misinterpreted “Cape 
<collectingCountry box="[1267,1389,824,848]" name="Saint Vincent and the Grenadines" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">St. Vincent</collectingCountry>
” as meaning “off 
<collectingCountry box="[418,513,856,880]" name="Portugal" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Portugal</collectingCountry>
”, i.e. the Cape 
<collectingCountry box="[673,794,856,880]" name="Saint Vincent and the Grenadines" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">St. Vincent</collectingCountry>
, which is the best known geographic feature of the south coast of 
<collectingCountry box="[334,428,888,912]" name="Portugal" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Portugal</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Stein D. L. &amp; Able K. J." box="[439,660,888,912]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="1275 - 1283" refId="ref44298" refString="Stein D. L. &amp; Able K. J. 1986. Liparididae. In: Whitehead P. J. P., Bauchot M. - L., Hureau J. - C., Nielsen J. &amp; Tortonese E. (eds) Fishes of the North-eastern Atlantic and Mediterranean (FNAM III). UNESCO, Paris, 1275 - 1283." type="book chapter" year="1986">Stein &amp; Able (1986)</bibRefCitation>
cited Lindberg. The species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gunther" authorityYear="1887" box="[972,1160,888,912]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Liparidae" genus="Paraliparis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="membranaceus">
<emphasis box="[972,1160,888,912]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">P. membranaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was omitted from the reviews of Chilean liparids (
<bibRefCitation author="Stein D. L. &amp; Melendez C. R. &amp; Kong U. I." box="[545,723,920,944]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="358 - 373" refId="ref44367" refString="Stein D. L., Melendez C. R. &amp; Kong U. I. 1991. A review of Chilean snailfishes (Liparididae, Scorpaeniformes) with descriptions of a new genus and three new species. Copeia 1991 (2): 358 - 373." type="journal article" year="1991">
Stein 
<emphasis box="[609,663,920,944]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">et al.</emphasis>
1991
</bibRefCitation>
) and of Southern Ocean species (
<bibRefCitation author="Andriashev A. P." box="[1083,1271,920,944]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="255 - 266" refId="ref38170" refString="Andriashev A. P. 1998. A review of recent studies of Southern Ocean Liparidae (Teleostei: Scorpaeniformes). Cybium, 22 (3): 255 - 266." type="journal article" year="1998">Andriashev 1998</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Andriashev A. P." box="[1282,1340,920,944]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="1 - 477" refId="ref38203" refString="Andriashev A. P. 2003. Liparid fishes (Liparidae, Scorpaeniformes) of the Southern Ocean and adjacent waters. Results of Russian Antarctic Expeditions 9. Explorations of the Fauna of the Seas, 53 (61): 1 - 477." type="journal article" year="2003">2003</bibRefCitation>
). The 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gunther" authorityYear="1887" box="[242,428,952,976]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Liparidae" genus="Paraliparis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="membranaceus">
<emphasis box="[242,428,952,976]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">P. membranaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
record off mainland 
<collectingCountry box="[648,738,952,976]" name="Portugal" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Portugal</collectingCountry>
is erroneous. For this reason this species is not included in this list.
</paragraph>
